  <Notes>
    <Note Caller="1" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References>
        <Reference>04601201700010</Reference>
      </References>
      <Content>It would, of course, be possible to interpret ὀφθαλμός in {S:04601201700010} as meaning simply ‘eye,’ and therefore one might translate ‘as if the whole body were an eye.’ But the following terms such as ἀκοή ({D:24.53}) and ὄσφρησις ({D:24.71}) indicate quite clearly that it is the sensory faculty or capacity which is involved.</Content>
    </Note>
