          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-12-16 10:50:49" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(a figurative extension of meaning of {L:ὀφθαλμός&lt;SDBG:ὀφθαλμός:000000&gt;}[a] ‘eye,’ {D:8.23}) capacity to understand as the result of perception</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to be able to understand</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to come to perceive</Gloss>
                <Gloss>understanding</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In both {S:04201904200036} and {S:04900101800006} ὀφθαλμός designates a faculty of understanding and is not a reference merely to perception. In {S:04900101800006} {L:καρδία&lt;SDBG:καρδία:000000&gt;} denotes the mind (see {D:26.3}), so that the phrase ‘the eyes of the mind’ really means ‘the capacity for understanding which the mind has.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
